MONROVIA, Jan. 20 (Xinhua) -- At least 30 people were killed on Wednesday night in a stampede caused by an attack on a religious gathering in a suburb of Monrovia, Liberia's capital, according to reports by local media on Thursday. A police spokesperson was quoted as saying that worshippers at a religious gathering in the New Kru town of Monrovia were attacked on Wednesday night by "criminals coming with knives", which created chaos and led to a stampede as everyone tried to escape.  â– 